sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1878001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: iRFP713 (the fluorescent protein formerly known as "iRFP")
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: iRFP713 is a Rhodopseudomonas palustris bacterial phytochrome photoreceptor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This fluorescent protein has an excitation wavelength of 690 nm and an emission wavelength of 713 nm. The extinction coefficient is 98000 M-1 cm-1. Its quantum yield is 6.3%. Its photostability half-life is 960 seconds. Its pKa is 4.5. Near-infrared fluorescent proteins are good for long-term in vivo imaging and exhibit high brightness in bacteria, mammalian cells, and mice.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The PstI site and EcoRI site within the reporter has been removed. There is a Bbs1 site within the coding sequence so be wary if using that enzyme for Golden Gate DNA assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Luke Garcia

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
